## First-session onboarding gate

**Before doing any other work**, check `.forge/onboarding.yaml`. If `status` is
`pending` or `in-progress`, run `/onboarding`. If `status` is `complete` or the file
does not exist, skip this section silently.

## Claude-specific addenda

The sections below apply only to the Claude Code runtime. All cross-runtime operating
rules live in AGENTS.md above and are not repeated here.

## Model tiering (advisory)

FORGE does **not** route between models — Claude Code's model picker is the only real
selection mechanism. Per FORGE Spec 316, tier-routing metadata was removed because
nothing read it. This section is operator advisory.

For cost-sensitive sessions, operators can manually switch to Haiku for these commands
without measurable quality loss:
- `/now`, `/session`, `/insights`, `/brainstorm`, `/note`, `/matrix` (display only)

These commands stay on the operator's default model:
- `/implement`, `/close`, `/spec`, `/trace`, `/forge`, `/parallel`, `/synthesize`

In regulated or high-stakes environments, run all commands on the default high-tier
model. See `docs/decisions/ADR-316-cost-framework-scope-reduction.md`.

## Context-aware file reading

1. **Reuse rule**: When a command says "Read" a file already read earlier this
   conversation with no edits since, use the in-context content instead of re-reading.
2. **Static files** (read at most once): `docs/process-kit/scoring-rubric.md`,
   `docs/process-kit/human-validation-runbook.md`, `docs/specs/_template.md`.
3. **Session context snapshot**: `/now` writes `docs/sessions/context-snapshot.md`;
   display-only commands read it if present and from today.

## Command execution discipline

> **Spec 265** — applies to every FORGE command. Governs output, not behavior.

1. **No routing narration.** Execute routing/feature-gated logic silently.
2. **`[mechanical]` steps are silent by default** unless they carry an explicit
   `print`/`report`/`display`/`emit` instruction.
3. **Unconfigured features do not exist.** Do not name, explain, or offer to enable a
   feature not present in `AGENTS.md` / `.forge/modules/`.
4. **Addenda are read conditionally.** Treat `## Addendum:` gates as binding.

See `docs/process-kit/command-authoring-guide.md`.

## Prompt caching (best-effort)

FORGE's static content qualifies for Anthropic prompt caching when the host runtime
supports it. Claude Code handles caching automatically for system-prompt content.

**Cache-eligibility** depends on edit cadence, not just file size:
- **High hit rate (>70%)**: `implement.md`, `trace.md`, `spec.md` (stable across session).
- **Low hit rate**: `close.md`, `session.md`, `now.md`, the active spec file (edited mid-session).

**Do not cache**: session logs, the active spec file mid-implementation, or any file
actively being edited. See `docs/process-kit/read-audit.md`.
{% if agent_sdk %}
### Prompt caching for direct API integrations

If your project calls the Anthropic API directly (Python `anthropic` SDK or TypeScript
`@anthropic-ai/sdk`), reduce token costs on repeated static content with prompt caching.
Add `cache_control: {"type": "ephemeral"}` to any content block (>1024 tokens, reused
within 5 minutes). Cache static system prompts and loaded spec files; do not cache
per-turn user messages or state that changes each request. Requires a current Sonnet or
Opus model — see the [Anthropic model documentation](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/about-claude/models).
See `docs/process-kit/prompt-caching-consumer-guide.md` for worked examples.
{% endif %}
