## Bash safety patterns (`set -e`)

All `.forge/` bash scripts use `set -euo pipefail`. These patterns silently break:

| Unsafe | Safe |
|--------|------|
| `[[ cond ]] && action` | `if [[ cond ]]; then action; fi` |
| `((counter++))` | `(( counter++ )) \|\| true` |
| `local var=$(cmd)` | `local var; var=$(cmd)` |

Resolve paths via `$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)` — scripts run from
temp dirs (copier, CI) where `$0` resolves to the caller's working directory.

## FORGE Mission

FORGE's mission is to make each individual developer the CEO of a continuously-optimizing
development company — strategic advisors and auditable process at every step, but the
developer decides what happens, when, and why.

